    "We have repeated our analysis of coverage for small training dataset, this time using ChEMBL as our structures of interest (Supplementary Fig. 12).",
    "Again, these plots may allow us spot coverage bias and restrictions to the domain of applicability.",
    "We have shown that the presented method for estimating MCES distances exhibits fairly small running times.",
    "It is however important to note that the current implementation is Python-based, with hardly any optimizations applied.",
    "We conjecture that a C++ implementation of the MCES bounds can reach running times comparable to that of RDKit's RASCAL implementation, as it consists primarily of computing a maximum matching, one of the best-studied problems in theoretical computer science."
